>Description:
On a Mac, dragging a non-frontmost window with the command key down should drag the window, but not bring it to the front.  In DrScheme, the window comes to the front.
This should be changed to conform to the Mac Human Interface guidelines.
>How-To-Repeat:
Bring up two windows in DrScheme.  Try to drag the rearmost by dragging its title bar with the command key down.  See that the window comes to the front as a side-effect of the drag.
